The paper describes propagation measurements for millimeter-wave (mmWave) bands, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The measurements are focused on small-cell base station diversity, which falls under the Mobile Computing (cs.MM) and Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses coordinated multipoint (CoMP) analysis, which is related to system-level optimization and falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
